<BODY>
<HEADLINE> US Understands Pakistan Better: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Foreign Minister
Abdul Sattar Wednesday said there is an improved understanding and
appreciation of Pakistan's perceptions and compulsions by the
United States.
</P>
<P>
The United States has noted Islamabad's national security
concerns, Sattar said while briefing the cabinet on his recent
visit to Washington and meetings with U.S.officials.
</P>
<P>
The cabinet met here under the chairmanship of Chief Executive
General Pervez Musharraf.
</P>
<P>
Sattar said his discussions with U.S. Deputy Secretary of State
Strobe Talbott on nuclear issues, which were the main purpose of
his visit to Washington, were satisfactory.
</P>
<P>
"The U.S. side appreciated steps taken by Pakistan to ensure
the custodial safety of strategic assets and prevent export of
sensitive technology," he said.
</P>
<P>
However, Washington "expressed regrets at the delay in Pakistan
's signing of the Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty (CTBT) which the
previous government had pledged it would do by September 1999," he
added.
</P>
<P>
According to Sattar, Washington also expressed satisfaction
over Pakistan's policy for the revival of the economy and measures
for the introduction of genuine democracy in the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
