<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 16 Killed in India-Controlled Kashmir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Sixteen people, including 13
militants, have been killed in India-controlled Jammu and Kashmir
since Tuesday evening, the Press Trust of India (PTI) reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Among the 13 slain militants, eight were "top ones," the PTI
quoted official sources in Srinagar, capital of India-controlled
Jammu and Kashmir, as saying.
</P>
<P>
In a gun battle with militants on Tuesday night, troops killed
six top militants belonging to the Lashkar-e-Toiba outfit, foiling
an infiltration bid along the border belt in the Poonch sector in
west Kashmir, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Local police Wednesday also claimed to have dealt a "severe
blow" to the pro-Pakistan Hizbul Mujahideen outfit by gunning down
two of the outfit's top militants in an exchange of fire in
Srinagar on Tuesday evening, the PTI added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
