<HEADLINE> U.S., Rwanda Sign Aid Agreements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 21 (Xinhua) -- The governments of Rwanda and the
United States signed three grant agreements worth 15.1 million
U.S. dollars on Wednesday, bringing the total of U.S. assistance
to 485 million dollars since 1994, Rwanda News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Rwandan Minister of Finance and Economic Planning Donald
Kaberuka and U. S. ambassador to Rwanda George Staples signed
these agreements in the Rwandan capital Kigali.
</P>
<P>
The funds granted through the U.S. Agency for International
Development is supposed to be disbursed in the areas of rule of
law and transparency in governance, health and social sector and
food security. 
</P>
</TEXT>
