<HEADLINE> Forest Fire Brought Under Control Near Atlantic Canada City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Halifax Regional Municipality officials said a slight rain
helped dozens of firefighters harness the fire that covered about
120 hectares north of the city, with the help of four water-
dropping helicopters.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 police were mobilized to help with evacuation at
the most dangerous Kingswood subdivision, where the fire burned to
within 60 meters of some homes with flames witnessed shooting up
to 10 meters in the air Wednesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Officials have lifted the evacuation order to allow evacuees
to return from makeshift shelters.
</P>
<P>
There have been no reports about casualties or damage. Police
attributed the fire to human error, saying it wasn't a naturally
caused fire. But they didn't give details about the cause.
