<HEADLINE> Pakistan's 2nd Naval Base Starts Functioning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's second naval base --
Jinnah Naval Base at Ormara in southwestern province of
Balochistan was inaugurated Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The new naval base, 240 kilometers to the west of the port city
of Karachi, was completed at a cost of 4.5 billion rupees (849
million U.S. dollars) and will provide berthing facilities to
eight ships and four submarines, reported the News Network
International agency here.
</P>
<P>
Inaugurating the base, Pakistan's Chief Executive General
Pervez Musharraf said the completion of Ormara naval base will
bring many new strategic, operational and economic benefits to the
country.
</P>
<P>
Ormara bisects the Mekran coast of Pakistan located almost same
distance from Karachi, home to the country's first naval base, and
Gwadar next to Pak-Iran border.
</P>
<P>
The base includes two finger piers and a marginal wharf and
onshore buildings. A consortium of international companies
including STFA of Turkey and DNA of Belgium was responsible for
the construction with STFA completing the major portion. 
</P>
</TEXT>
