<HEADLINE> French Parliament Adopts Law on Reinforcing Fight Against Cults </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 22 (Xinhua) -- The French National Assembly, or
lower house of parliament, adopted unanimously on Thursday a law
on reinforcing the fight against cults by regarding any act of ``
mental manipulation'' as a crime.
</P>
<P>
The draft law first came from the French Senate, the upper
house of parliament, and was approved by the Minister of Justice
Elisabeth Guigou.
</P>
<P>
The law calls for the dissolution of all the cults which have
been condemned twice by the justice.
</P>
<P>
It bans propaganda by the cults in communication channels
accessible to the young people and authorizes the local municipal
governments to ban the establishment of cults in schools,
hospitals and other places which shelter people vulnerable to cult
propaganda.
</P>
</TEXT>
