<HEADLINE> Philippine Sports Leaders Sign Statement of Understanding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 22 (Xinhua) -- In the observance of the "Olympic
Truce" and "to promote culture of peace and prosperity for the
furtherance of Philippine sports," the leaders of the country's
three top sports agencies signed Thursday a statement of
understanding.
</P>
<P>
Philippine Sports Commission (PSC) chairman Carlos Tuason and
Philippine Olympic Committee president Celso Dayrit formally
signed the agreement at the PSC Chairman's office in Manila.
</P>
<P>
Presidential adviser for youth and sports Richard Gomez was not
present during the signing but Tuason said the actor/sportsman has
already signed the three-page statement before Gomez left for
United States Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The statement of understanding bound the sports leaders to
promote a culture of peace, harmony, cooperation and teamwork
among all sectors involved with the promotion and development of
Philippine sports.
</P>
<P>
The leaders also pledged in the agreement to coordinate and
support each other's role and jurisdition in the promotion and
development of the country's athletes leading to their
participation in international competitions. 
</P>
