<HEADLINE> World's 1st Movie-based Mobile Phone Game Available in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
All the characters and concepts of 'Titan A.E.,' the world's
first interactive movie-based battle game, are based on an
animated film from Twentieth Century Fox under the same name.
</P>
<P>
It is also the fruit of cooperation between New World Mobility,
Twentieth Century Fox and Finland-based wireless entertainment
publishing company Riot Entertainment, which is responsible for
the design of the game.
</P>
<P>
"The 'Titan A.E. game is designed to be played on the mobile
phone so that users can play the game wherever they are," said New
World Telephone Group Chief Executive Albert Wong at a press
conference.
</P>
<P>
"This new 'Titan A.E.' game is in line with New World Mobility'
s long-term business vision - to provide quality mobile services
to our customers, including mobile entertainment," Wong said.
</P>
<P>
He said his company will make the game available to its WAP
users soon and will continue to roll out more high quality
services, including WAP and third generation services. 
</P>
</TEXT>
