<DOCNO> XIE20000622.0071 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bill on Surrogacy Still in Dispute Among Legco Members </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Surrogacy, pregnancy by artificial insemination or surgical
implantation of a fertilized egg, is a very complicated and
sensitive issue, said the Secretary for Health and Welfare E.K.
Yeoh, in response to the committee stage amendments moved to the
Human Reproductive Technology Bill in the Legislative Council.
</P>
<P>
"We understand that some people may not accept this matter
because of various reasons including religious or ethical
considerations," Yeoh said.
</P>
<P>
"However, we must admit that in some circumstances surrogacy is
the only hope for a couple to have their own biological child e.g.
the woman's womb is removed because of disease," Yeoh stressed.
</P>
<P>
In view of the availability of the enabling reproductive
technology, it is imperative to consider giving these couples a
fair chance to have their offspring, Yeoh added.
</P>
<P>
"Having said that, I must speak with assertion that we are not
encouraging surrogacy. In fact, our policy is to actively
discourage surrogacy, as evidenced in the stringent control of
surrogacy arrangement in the Human Reproductive Technology Bill,"
the secretary explained.
</P>
<P>
Law makers agreed to impose strict regulation through
legislation as there is currently no legislative control over
surrogacy, but they said they yet allow a leeway for those who
have but to resort to this option.
</P>
<P>
"In particular, we want to ensure that surrogacy on commercial
basis is strictly prohibited," they emphasized.
</P>
<P>
In Hong Kong, surrogacy remains a rather un-conventional option
that even many infertile couples will rarely consider. For those
who resort to this method to have their offspring, very few are
willing to discuss it openly, mainly on grounds of privacy or the
taboo nature of the subject.
</P>
<P>
They said that there will be an Ethics Committee set up under
the future Council on Reproductive Technology to, among other
things, monitor and assess the public's ethical and moral
attitudes towards surrogacy arrangements.
</P>
<P>
The Bill aims to regulate reproductive technology procedure,
use of embryos and gametes for research and other purposes, to
regulate surrogacy arrangement and to establish a Council on Human
Reproductive Technology.
</P>
<P>
The purpose of legislation is to ensure, through statutory
measures, that reproductive technology will be safely practiced
and the rights of users and children born out of reproductive
technology procedure will be duly protected.
</P>
<P>
According to the bill, the procedure will be restricted to
married couples and prohibit commercial dealing of the use of
gametes and embryos. Commercial arrangement of surrogacy should
also be an offense.
</P>
<P>
"Although there have been varying views on some controversial
subjects, we have already taken into consideration views from
majority of the community when finalizing the regulatory framework,
" Yeoh said.
</P>
<P>
One important consensus law makers have reached with the Bills
Committee in the deliberation of this Bill is that the welfare of
the child to be born should be regarded as paramount importance.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
