<HEADLINE> Annan Arrives in Damascus on Peace Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, June 22 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary General Kofi Annan
arrived here Thursday afternoon, on the first visit by a high-
ranking international official to Syria since the funeral of late
Syrian President Hafez al-Assad on June 13.
</P>
<P>
Upon arrival at Damascus international airport, Annan told
reporters that he will discuss with Syrian officials the latest
developments in south Lebanon and the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
"In Lebanon, we worked with the concerned parties for the
application of the U.N. resolution 425," Annan said.
</P>
<P>
He also urged the parties involved in the peace process to apply
the two Security Council resolutions 242 and 338, which call for
Israel to withdraw its forces from occupied territories.
</P>
<P>
Annan was greeted at the airport by Syrian Foreign Minister
Faruk Shareh.
</P>
<P>
Damascus is the last leg in Annan's Middle East tour which has
already taken him to Iran, Egypt, Lebanon, Jordan, Israel and
Palestinian self-rule areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
