<HEADLINE> Silver, Gold Down in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ready silver (.999 fineness) closed at 7,920 rupees (184.18 U.S.
dollars) per kilogram, showing a fall of 45 rupees (1.05 dollars)
over the last close of 7,965 rupees (185.23 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Raw silver (.916 fineness) declined by 25 rupees (0.58 dollar)
to closed at 7,805 rupees (181.51 dollars) per kg from 7,830
rupees (182.09 dollars).
</P>
<P>
Standard gold and twenty-two-carat gold showed a fresh fall of
5 rupees (0.12 dollar) at 4,575 rupees (106.40 dollars) per 10
grams and 4,230 rupees (98.37 dollars) as against Wednesday's
close of 4,580 rupees (106.52 dollars) and 4,235 rupees (98.49
dollars) respectively. 
</P>
