<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Requests Probe Into Deaths of Illegals in Britain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 22 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese embassy in London has
asked the British authorities to conduct a serious investigation
into the deaths of 58 illegal immigrants and bring the masterminds
to book.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued on Wednesday, the embassy said it was
informed by the British police on Tuesday that the two survivors
were initially confirmed as Chinese and the 58 victims were also
believed by police to be from China.
</P>
<P>
The bodies of 58 illegal immigrants were found in the back of a
truck at England's southern port of Dover early on Monday.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese government consistently opposes human trafficking
and illegal immigration in whatever form and firmly condemns the
evil, money-motivated acts of human trafficking gangs, who pay no
heed to the victims' lives," said the statement.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government is willing to coordinate with all
foreign governments concerned in jointly cracking down on cross-
border human trafficking, it said.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese embassy much regrets and is grieved that the
illegal immigrants readily believed what the 'snake heads' had
said and took the risk which cost them their lives. We express our
solicitude to the families of the victims," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The embassy also promised cooperation with the British side in
handling the aftermath of the incident.
</P>
<P>
The driver of the Dutch-registered truck, which arrived from
Zeebrugge, Belgium, just before midnight, has been arrested.
</P>
<P>
The dead, 54 men and four women, were in their early 20s. The
two survivors, both men, have been taken to hospital and
questioned. They admitted that they came from Fujian, China.
</P>
<P>
Suffocation was suspected for the deaths.
</P>
<P>
The truck was an airtight 18-meter-long container which was
partially loaded with fresh tomatoes. Its refrigerating unit was
not switched on and the interior temperature was high. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
