<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 13 Dead in Yangtze Shipwreck (More Added) EDS-More Added </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Rescue workers have retrieved 13
bodies and saved 51 other passengers from a ship which sank on the
Yangtze River near Luzhou in southwest China's Sichuan Province
early this morning.
</P>
<P>
According to witnesses and survivors, the passenger vessel "
Rong Jian", which was only capable of holding 101 people, was
carrying about 200 passengers when it hit a rock while sailing in
foggy conditions.
</P>
<P>
The wreck was carried further downstream.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said that the ship was only capable of carrying about
70 people safely in the flood season, and the main reason for the
accident was overloading.
</P>
<P>
Wang Jingxiang, deputy governor of Sichuan Province, said that
related departments of the provincial and local prefectural
governments sent rescue teams to the spot immediately after
hearing about the accident.
</P>
<P>
So far, 19 ships and hundreds of rescue workers are continuing
search along the river for survivors and bodies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
