<HEADLINE> China Unicom Debuts on HK Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The stock opened at 16.78 HK dollars, almost 10 percent up from
its initial public offering (IPO) price of 15.42 HK dollars, and
stood around the 16.90 level minutes after the opening.
</P>
<P>
Yang Xianzu, Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of China
Unicom, said at the launch ceremony that the successful listing of
China Unicom in Hong Kong and the United States is an important
step in the company's journey into the international market.
</P>
<P>
"It is a new starting point for the development of China Unicom
and is of great importance," said Yang. He promised to maximize
the benefit of the investors.
</P>
<P>
China Unicom, China's no. 2 telecommunications provider second
only to China Telecommunications, offered 2.4 billion shares
globally, and in Hong Kong, 122 million shares, to raise 4.92
billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
One day before its Hong Kong listing, China Unicom stocks began
trading on the U.S. market at 22 U.S. dollars a share, then rose
to as high as 24.63 before closing at 22.125 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
China Unicom was set up in 1993 and grew rapidly with strong
support from the government. The company now boasts 14 percent of
the Chinese domestic market and its mobile Telecom network
subscribers had reached 10.1 million as of June this year.
</P>
<P>
China Unicom is involved in a wide range of businesses, from
mobile telecommunications, paging, fixed telephones, to data and
Internet services. 
</P>
</TEXT>
