<HEADLINE> Sino-French Pharmaceutical Venture Set Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 22 (Xinhua) -- China Huajin Pharmaceutical Co.
and Servier Pharmaceutical Corp. of France signed an agreement
here today to set up a joint venture in Tianjin Municipality.
</P>
<P>
The new Servier Tianjin Pharmaceutical Co., Ltd., with an
investment of 130 million yuan, is located in the economic and
technological development zone in Tianjin, a port city near
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the company premises, covering an area of 37,
000 sq m, will start in October, and the company is expected to
turn out medical products in 2003. 
</P>
