<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, June 22 (Xinhua) -- A luxury ocean liner, the "
Shuangyuxing", was launched today on its maiden voyage from this
capital of China's southernmost Hainan Province to Haiphong, a
coastal city in Viet Nam.
</P>
<P>
Cruises on the liner are managed by the island province's
international travel agency, which will offer three voyages a week,
starting October 1 this year.
</P>
<P>
The liner, with a displacement of 40,000 tons, contains 776
guest rooms, and can accommodate 2,019 tourists at a time.
