<HEADLINE> Foreign Minister Tang, Albright Hold Talks (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
They also agreed to make preparations for meetings between the
two presidents during the UN Millennium Summit and the APEC
informal summit meeting.
</P>
<P>
Tang said during the talks that through the concerted efforts
of both sides, especially with the care and stimulating efforts of
the heads of two state, Sino-US relations have witnessed
improvement and development in the past few years. Not long ago,
President Jiang Zemin and President Bill Clinton exchanged views
through the hotline on bilateral relations, and this is of great
significance to the bilateral relationship, he said.
</P>
<P>
So long as both sides strictly observe the basic norms
governing international relations, including mutual respect for
national sovereignty and territorial integrity, and non-
interference in each other's internal affairs, and handle
bilateral relations with a spirit of equality, mutual benefit and
seeking common ground while preserving differences, their
relationship can undoubtedly continue to move forward, Tang said.
</P>
<P>
He said this year serves as a link between the preceding and
the following periods, and China is willing to join hands with the
US to push forward ties, in a bid to create a sound foundation for
the two countries' relationship in the new century.
</P>
<P>
Albright concurred with Tang's remarks on bilateral relations.
She said that relations with China are among the most important
foreign relations of the US government, and the hotline
conversation between the heads of the two states has shown once
again that the maintenance of regular contact between top leaders
plays an extremely important role in the bilateral relationship.
The US side is willing to work together with China for the further
progress of relations, she said.
</P>
