<HEADLINE> Foreign Minister Tang, Albright Hold Talks (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China is determined to, and confident and capable of
safeguarding the country's sovereignty and territorial integrity,
and of realizing the complete reunification of the country, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Albright said the US sticks to the One-China Policy, abides by
its "three nos" commitment, namely, not to support Taiwan's
independence, not to support "two Chinas" or "one China, one
Taiwan", not to support Taiwan's entry into any international
organization requiring sovereign states for membership, and
opposes the Taiwan Security Enhancement Act proposed by certain US
congress members.
</P>
<P>
Tang said the Chinese side attaches great importance to the
attitude the US has made clear, and hopes that the US would take
practical measures to adhere to the One-China Policy, the three
joint communiques and the relevant commitments it has made, adding
that this is of critical importance to the further development of
bilateral relations and the stability of the Taiwan straits
situation.
</P>
<P>
Tang and Albright also exchanged views on China's permanent
normal trade relations with the US, and agreed that to conduct
cooperation in certain important sectors would help the
improvement of ties. The two highly evaluated the Sino-US
Statement on Cooperation on the Environment and Development, and
the Agreement on Mutual Legal Assistance in Criminal Matters
signed recently. The Chinese side also reaffirmed its principled
stance on issues including human rights and the prevention of
nuclear proliferation.
</P>
<P>
On the issue of international security, Tang said the National
Missile Defense (NMD) system proposed by the US would have a
serious negative impact on the global strategic balance and
stability, and efforts for international arms control, disarmament
and prevention of nuclear proliferation. The Chinese side urges
the US side to earnestly respond to the international appeal and
to abandon its NMD plan as early as possible, Tang said. 
</P>
