<HEADLINE> Cipollini to Miss Tour de France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ROME, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Italian Mario Cipollini will miss
the Tour de France after a crash in training earlier this month,
reports said here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Cipollini cracked two ribs and hurt his chin in a fall in
training in Tuscany on June 10. The facial injury needed 30
stitches.
</P>
<P>
Cipollini hoped to be able to resume training in a few days
and aimed to be fit enough to race in the Tour of Spain which runs
from August 26 to September 17. 
