<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Holland Sets Up Dairy Industry Center In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, June 22 (Xinhua) -- A dairy industry training and
demonstration center has been set up jointly by Holland and China
in the suburbs of this capital of central China's Henan Province.
</P>
<P>
Both sides shared the 16 million yuan (nearly two million U.S.
dollars) investment in the project, which occupies some 70 ha of
land and contains three cattle farms and 47 pastures.
</P>
<P>
According to a five-year agreement reached by the two sides,
the center will introduce advanced technologies and facilities
from Holland to Henan, as well as help train local farmers.
</P>
<P>
The new center is the third agricultural assistance project for
China that Holland has joined, a local official source said.
</P>
</TEXT>
