<HEADLINE> Shanghai Grants New Powers to Pudong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 22 (Xinhua) -- The Standing Committee of the
People's Congress of Shanghai today decided to setup the Peop's
Congress of Pudong New District, a 10-year-old development zone.
</P>
<P>
According to the decision, the first People's Congress of the
Pudong New District will soon be convened to elect its own
standing committee of 29 members, the magistrate and deputy
magistrates, the president of the district court and the chief
procurator of the district procutatorate.
</P>
<P>
The predecessor of the Pudong New District was the Pudong New
Area, which is located in the eastern part of Shanghai across the
Bund and was set up in 1990 as part of the central government's
efforts to speed up the economic development of this, the largest
metropolis in China.
</P>
<P>
Since 1993, it has been managed by the Administrative Committee
of the Pudong New Area, which is directly under the municipal
government. Until now, it has not had its own legislative,
administrative or judicial bodies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
