<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chongqing, Seoul Connected by Air </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, June 22 (Xinhua) -- The first direct air route
between this southwest China municipality and Seoul, capital of
the Republic of Korea (ROK), opened today.
</P>
<P>
The one-way flight takes about three hours and a half.
</P>
<P>
Starting today, Asiana Airlines of the ROK will operate a one-
way flight each Thursday, using A321 aircraft. From the middle of
July, the Chongqing branch of China Southwest Airlines will
operate two-way flights each Wednesday and Friday, using Boeing
planes.
</P>
<P>
Local travel service officials said that the direct flights
will encourage more people from South Korea to visit the world-
famous scenic spots in southwest China.
</P>
<P>
As the nation's largest municipality, Chongqing has already
opened direct air routes to about 50 domestic cities, and Hong
Kong, Macao, Bangkok, Munich and other major cities around the
world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
