<DOCNO> XIE20000622.0119 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese, Iranian Presidents Hold Talks (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Khatami reiterated Iran's adherence to the one-China Policy,
for which Jiang expressed his appreciation.
</P>
<P>
After listening to Khatami's advocacy of dialogue between
civilizations, Jiang rated it highly and said that he was pleased
to find this idea positively supported by many countries. He noted
that the United Nations has designated the year 2001 as the year
of dialogue between civilizations.
</P>
<P>
Since assuming his post, President Khatami has adhered to a
foreign policy of eliminating tension and implementing dialogue
between civilizations, and has made efforts to improve relations
with neighboring countries as well as with the European countries,
Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
China appreciates the fact that significant progress has been
achieved in these aspects, and hopes that Iran will score greater
achievements in maintaining regional peace and stability, Jiang
added. 
