<DOCNO> XIE20000622.0129 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Book on Japan's Aggression of China Found </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, June 22 (Xinhua) -- A book on Japan's aggression of
China during World War II has been discovered in central China's
Henan Province.
</P>
<P>
The book, published by the then Japanese Military contains
battle records and the general situation in north China at the
time. The records give a full account of some 50 battles in China
between 1937-38 led by the Lugouqiao Incident, which marked the
beginning of Japan's all-out war of aggression against China
between 1937-1945.
</P>
<P>
The general situation of north China provides information on
the environment, economics, the distribution of populations, urban
construction, and historical sites in Hebei, Shandong, Shanxi
provinces, and other places.
</P>
<P>
The book provides more evidence of Japan's invasion of China.
</P>
</TEXT>
