<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Ends Firmer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 22 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar bumped back
above 60 U.S. cents to end firmer Thursday.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the Australian dollar was at 60.11 U.S. cents,
from 59.96 at the end of the local session Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The currency traded between a low of 60 U.S. cents and a high
of 60.24.
</P>
<P>
It dipped below the 60 figure for most of the local session
Wednesday, then made back the losses during offshore trading
Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
The euro fell foul of the market Wednesday night as it failed
to extend a rally, slipping to a low of 94.43 U.S. cents.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar's movements often follow closely the path
of the euro.
</P>
<P>
Also at the close, the Australian dollar was at 0.6352 euro
from 0.6292 at Wednesday's close and 63.36 Japanese yen from 63.10.
</P>
