<HEADLINE> Keim, Davison Earn Olympic Diving Berths </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Jenny Keim and Michelle Davison
earned their berths for the Sydney Olympics after finishing 1-2 in
the Olympic diving trials here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Keim, a 22-year-old from Miami, won women's three-meter
springboard trials with 860.31 points and Davion took the other
spot with 844.59 points.
</P>
<P>
Michelle Rojohn, who was competing in her first trials, missed
the second spot by 4.56 points. She finished third with 840.03
points.
</P>
<P>
Keim and Davison were 1-2 after the semifinals a day earlier
and they stayed that way throughout the five-dive final at King
County Aquatic Center.
</P>
<P>
In the men's three-meter semifinals, Troy Dumais was first and
David Pichler was second.
</P>
</TEXT>
