<HEADLINE> Grassroots Courts in China Urged to Ensure Justice </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Lu Gan, a senior Party official
in charge of legal construction in China, said here today that
grassroots courts must ensure that justice prevails.
</P>
<P>
"The people's courts at various levels should put justice above
everything else," said Luo, secretary of the Committee of
Political Science and Law Under the Chinese Communist Party (CPC)
Central Committee, at a national conference on court work.
</P>
<P>
Luo is also a member of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central
Committee.
</P>
<P>
He said that courts should provide judicial guarantees and
legal services for the development of China's social productive
forces, and for the fundamental interests of the overwhelming
majority of the Chinese people.
</P>
<P>
Under the leadership of the CPC Central Committee, courts
across the country have made steady progress in enhancing
professional quality over the years, he said.
</P>
<P>
However, corruptive practices exist among some court employees,
and violations against the law take place from time to time,
undermining the reputation of courts and judges and tarnishing the
image of the Party and government, he said.
</P>
<P>
"The Party should strengthen its leadership role over court
work, and support the independent judicial power of courts and
judging panels," he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
