<HEADLINE> Subsidies for Laid Offs, Retirees Guaranteed in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 22 (Xinhua) -- The government's efforts to ensure
the issuance of subsidies for factory layoffs and pension-holders
have played an important part in facilitating the reforms of
enterprises and ensuring economic development.
</P>
<P>
This was learned at the opening of a two-day national
conference attended by heads of provincial-level labor and social
security bureaus across the country.
</P>
<P>
According to official figures, by the end of May, China had 6.
82 million workers laid off from state-owned enterprises, of whom
96 percent have been registered at re-employment centers and 90
percent provided with government subsidies.
</P>
<P>
Ninety-eight percent of retired laid-off workers have received
their pension on time.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, the number of employees under the umbrella of
pension insurance has reached 97.69 million, an increase of 2.67
million compared with the figure by the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
In 1998, the central leadership ordered governments at all
levels to ensure that sufficient subsidies and pension to the
layoffs and retirees be provided. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
