<HEADLINE> Air Crash Killing 42 in Central China (Details Added) EDS-More Added </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, June 22 (Xinhua) -- A passenger aircraft of Wuhan
Airlines crashed this afternoon in central China's Hubei Province,
killing all 42 on board including four crew members and 38
passengers.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred at about 15:00 PM, when the landing Y-7
passenger plane, B3479, from Enshi City, southwest of Hubei, to
Wuhan, the provincial capital, was hit by thunders, exploded in
the air, and crashed near Sitai Village of Yongfeng Township in
Hanyang District, Wuhan, according to local sources.
</P>
<P>
Local people, led by city leaders, are busy with rescuing.
Investigation into the cause of the accident is underway. 
