<HEADLINE> SW China City to Have More Foreign Missions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Chongqing, the largest city in
China's southwest, is expected to have more consulates from
developed countries, reported today's overseas edition of the "
People's Daily".
</P>
<P>
The newspaper said that as more multinational companies eye
China's western regions as a potential market, their governments
plan to establish consulates there.
</P>
<P>
Among big cities in the west, Chongqing Municipality is the
most favored choice. Japan and Canada already have consulates in
the city and Britain set up the consulate earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
Germany and Australia and other countries have shown interest
in opening their diplomatic offices in China's western regions,
said the newspaper.
</P>
<P>
Chen Xiao, director with the Chongqing's Foreign Affairs Office,
said that the city, located between affluent east China and
resource-rich west China, will help foreign missions serve to
expand businesses in western areas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
