<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Bank Governor Commits Corruption  Practices: Attorney General </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Governor of Bank Indonesia ordered reimbursement of Bank Bali
claim whereas the valid conditions for such reimbursement were not
fulfilled," Darusman told reporters before attending a cabinet
meeting in the presidential office.
</P>
<P>
He noted that prosecutors has found preliminary evidences to
confirm that the governor had committed corruption practices.
</P>
<P>
He also stressed that the detention of Sabirin was purely a
matter of law enforcement. "There is no pressure in the decision
to detain Sabirin," he added.
</P>
<P>
