</P>
<P>
-- Egypt's National Council for Women on Thursday will sign a
cooperation agreement with the United Nations Development Program.
</P>
<P>
The pact provides for the development of the council's
personnel, helping its technical committee as well as furthering
cooperation between the council and non-governmental organizations
to help women participate at the political level.
</P>
<P>
Al Akhbar:
</P>
<P>
-- Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa received on Wednesday
Israeli Knesset (parliament) member Yussi Katz and discussed the
Middle East peace process and the future of Israeli-Arab relations
in particular.
</P>
<P>
