<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Lower in Tokyo on Profit-Taking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Stock prices closed moderately lower
in Tokyo Thursday on profit-taking following their recent sharp
gains.
</P>
<P>
The Nikkei Stock Average of 225 selected issues on the First
Section of the Tokyo Stock lost 104.07 points, or 0.60 percent
from Wednesday's close to end at 17,106.01, after gaining nearly
900 points during the previous three days.
</P>
<P>
The broader-based Tokyo Stock Price Index, covering all First
Section issues, dropped 8.32 points or 0.53 percent to 1,575.63.
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the major section decreased to 671.02 million
shares from Wednesday's 696.06 million shares.
</P>
<P>
Hitachi was the day's volume leader.
</P>
<P>
Market sentiment remained good despite the overall fall in
share prices, supported by recent stability in New York share
prices, particularly that in the Nasdaq composite index, traders
said.
</P>
<P>
Several information and high-tech issues succumbed to profit-
taking.
</P>
<P>
Air transportation, retail and steel sectors marked large
declines, while real estate firms and consumer finance companies
drew buying.
</P>
<P>
Of the issues listed on the First Section, losers outnumbered
gainers 759 to 515, with 129 issues closing unchanged.  
</P>
</TEXT>
