<DOCNO> XIE20000622.0236 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinjiang to Use More Natural Gas-Fueled Motor Vehicles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, June 22 (Xinhua) -- The Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous
Region in northwest China plans to raise the number of natural gas-
fueled motor vehicles to 8,000 in the next five years, hoping to
prevent further deterioration of its worsening atmospheric
pollution.
</P>
<P>
The regional capital of Urumqi is one of the most heavily
polluted cities in the world. Exhaust fumes are blamed as the
major source of the problem.
</P>
<P>
In 1994, the regional government began to promote the use of
natural gas as fuel for motor vehicles instead of gasoline and
diesel oil. By last year, over 1,000 natural gas-fueled motor
vehicles were in use in Urumqi, and another 200 in cities
elsewhere in Xinjiang, sources said.
</P>
<P>
As a clean energy, natural gas can help control the worsening
air pollution in urban areas of the region and has been widely
used.
</P>
<P>
"Conversion of automobile fuel systems to accommodate natural
gas isn't difficult and costs only about 5,000 to 8,000 yuan,"
said Fang Jianye, a garage owner who does such work, adding that
one year of operation of the environment-friendly vehicles will
cover the cost.
</P>
<P>
The regional government will build more natural gas stations
and also offer low-interest loans for gas-driven vehicle buyers.
</P>
<P>
Xinjiang is rich in natural gas and has verified 817.7 billion
cubic meters of natural gas reserves. The increased use of natural
gas motor vehicles will help boost the natural gas market.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000622.0237 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Co. Able to Connect Mobile Phones with Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 22 (Xinhua) -- China has mastered key technology
for connecting the Internet with mobile phones -- the WAP (
wireless application protocol) network.
</P>
<P>
The technology was developed by the Beijing Guoyan Telecom
Technology Company Ltd.
</P>
<P>
The company put on show a series of services by the WAP network,
including mobile office, mobile stock exchange, news reports and
weather forecasts, at a press conference held here today.
</P>
<P>
WAP technology was known by only a few leading mobile phone
manufacturers including Ericsson, Nokia and Motorola. The foreign
companies, however, face big challenges in entering the Chinese
market in terms of localization, habits of Chinese users and
government policies.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Guoyan Company, cooperating with Beijing Posts and
Telecom University, has become the first Chinese telecom
enterprise that has the intellectual rights of the WAP network,
following nearly ten months of research. 
</P>
</TEXT>
