<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Boca Juniors Beat Palmeiras in Final to Win Copa Libertadores </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAO PAULO, June 21 (Xinhua) -- After a scoreless 90-minute
regular play, Boca Juniors of Argentina beat Palmeiras 4-2 in a
penalty session to clinch the Copa Libertadores Tournament here
Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
Boca Juniors goalkeeper Cordoba successfully blocked two
powerful shots by Asprilla and Roque Junior to guarantee the
victory for his team, which didn't miss any of its first four
shots.
</P>
<P>
Before the game, Palmeiras coach Luiz Felipe Scolari had
predicted that the Argentine team would play a predominantly
defensive game, and that his team would go on the offensive.
</P>
<P>
But the games was played in an entirely different way. From
the beginning, Boca Juniors went on the attack, catching the
Palmeiras players by surprise and forcing them to go on the
defensive.
</P>
<P>
The Boca Juniors' offensive game almost bore fruit in the
fourth minute, when defender Arrubarrena fired the ball into the
net. But referee Epifanio Gonzalez of Paraguay ruled the goal
unvalid as the player was offsides.
</P>
<P>
Palmeiras was about to turn things around when it switched from
defensive to offensive mode right after the start of the second
half.
</P>
<P>
For some 25 minutes, the Brazilians launched one attack after
another on the Argentine defense.
</P>
<P>
In the 48th minute striker Asprilla was knocked down in front
of the goal when he was to score. But it was not ruled a penalty.
</P>
<P>
Boca nearly scored on several hard-found occasions in the half,
but the ball would either go wild or was blocked by Palmeiras
defense. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
