<HEADLINE> Crisis in Bangladeshi Export Processing Zone Deepens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 22 (Xinhua) -- The crisis in the towel producing
industries located in the Chittagong Export Processing Zone (CEPZ)
further deepened on Wednesday as 12,000 workers of seven units
abstained from their duties to support the recent move by their
fellows in the towel industries.
</P>
<P>
The agitating workers of the 7 towel factories locked the doors
of those industries Wednesday and staged a sit-in demonstration in
front of their respective unit and the CEPZ office simultaneously,
the Independent reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Besides, over 5000 workers have already started hunger strike
unto death in front of their respective office, CEPZ office and
the Chittagong Press Club simultaneously since Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Earlier the management of the towel producing industries group
had notified over 4000 workers of its three units in the CEPZ to
resume their duties by Wednesday, otherwise, the absentee workers
would be terminated from June 21.
</P>
<P>
The workers of the towel industries in the CEPZ areas are
demanding for getting a raise in pay, as well as trade union
rights now banned in the zone.
</P>
<P>
Due to the actions taken by the striking workers, the mills
have suffered huge losses.
</P>
<P>
Of the total number of 11 towel industries in the CEPZ, one is
Bangladeshi, one Korean while the remaining 9 are Pakistani.
</P>
</TEXT>
