<DOCNO> XIE20000622.0257 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China News Digest: West on the Move (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chinese archaeologists have discovered a site of Qijia Culture
in northwest China's Qinghai Province.
</P>
<P>
The Qijia Culture flourished in the transition period from the
Neolithic Age to the Bronze Age, some 3,500 to 4,000 years ago,
according to the Qinghai Provincial Archaeological Research
Institute.
</P>
<P>
The ruins are located in Lajia Village, Minhe County, on the
upper reaches of the Yellow River, believed to be the first of its
kind ever found in China.
</P>
<P>
Booming Tourism Threatens Mogao Grottoes: Expert
</P>
<P>
Fan Jinshi has devoted half of her life to Dunhuang studies.
After decades of working on manuscripts and books and burying
herself in archives, she is now turning to computers to preserve
the famous Mogao caves located in northwest China.
</P>
<P>
The 62-year-old director of the China Dunhuang Studies
Institute envisages people being able to see the caves with the
help of CD ROMS and by doing so preserve some of the most precious
and priceless Buddhists artifacts in the world.
</P>
<P>
"Although the world's most advanced technology is being used to
protect the Mogao Grottoes, the caves are nonetheless
deteriorating amidst booming tourism in the area," said Fan.
</P>
<P>
This year marks the centennial anniversary of the discovery of
the Mogao caves located in Gansu Province along the trade route
known as the "Silk Road".
</P>
<P>
Secluded Grottoes to Open to Visitors
</P>
<P>
The Yunlin Grottoes, a major yet secluded part of the renowned
Dunhuang Caves in the northwest China province of Gansu, are
expected to open to visitors soon.
</P>
<P>
With a five-year consolidation project costing over seven
million yuan nearing its end, the grottoes are expected to first
open to visitors as part of a series of activities to be held to
mark the 100th anniversary of the discovery of the Sutras Cave at
Dunhuang.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the resplendent and magnificent frescoes in the
Mogao Grottoes, the murals in the Yulin Grottoes are simple and
elegant. Different in general tone as they are, the two groups of
grottoes are closely related in carving, fresco content and
artistic style, said Wang Wanfu, a deputy director in charge of
preservation work at the Dunhuang Research Academy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000622.0258 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China News Digest: West on the Move (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 22 (Xinhua) -- China has adopted a strategy of
developing its vast western areas, making it a key task in the
national economy this year and in the years to come. The following
are major events on western development this week:
</P>
<P>
SW China Improves Environment
</P>
<P>
The environment in southwest China 's Yunnan Province has been
improved, according to a latest government bulletin.
</P>
<P>
According to the bulletin, although 11 percent of lakes in the
province are getting worse, 23.5 percent have improved their
quality of water in the past year.
</P>
<P>
Some famous tourist attractions like the Erhai Lake, the Luguhu
Lake and the Fuxianhu Lake are so clean that their water can be
directly used as drinking water sources, the bulletin said.
</P>
<P>
The upper reaches of the province's major rivers have been
prevented from pollution. Air quality in 59 percent of the
province's cities reported 1st or 2nd class air quality.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing Kicks Off Massive Environmental Project
</P>
<P>
Chongqing Municipality, southwest China, has kicked off a 50
billion yuan environmental project to turn itself into a garden
city in the next 10 years.
</P>
<P>
City mayor Bao Xuding said that the project will focus on air
pollution in the urban area, treatment of industrial waste water,
and turning hillside fields into forested land along the Yangtze
River where the gigantic Three Gorges Reservoir will be located.
</P>
<P>
Bao said that the city will build two shelter forests which are
300 to 500 meters wide in the eastern and western urban zones.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing, covering 82,000 square kilometers and with a
population of 30 million, only has an afforestated area of 23
percent, but the soil eroded area accounts for 63 percent of its
total land area, 25 percentage points higher than the national
average.
</P>
<P>
China Builds Largest Botanical Garden in Yunnan
</P>
<P>
China has begun construction of its largest botanical garden in
Xishuangbanna in southwestern Yunnan Province.
</P>
<P>
This is another major step adopted by China in protecting its
diversified biological resources. The garden will collect plants
species from tropical and subtropical zones worldwide and protect
endangered species.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the garden, jointly sponsored by the Chinese
Academy of Sciences and Yunnan, is set to be completed in 2004. By
then, the garden will have 10,000 plant varieties bred from the
more than 4,000 types of plants in the Xishuangbanna Tropical Zone
Botanical Garden.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000622.0259 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Promote Software Export </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, June 22 (Xinhua) -- The Export Promotion Bureau (EPB) of
Bangladesh has formulated a draft recommendation simplifying the
conditionalities for providing interest-free loan to software
developing firms, the Financial Express reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
For promoting software export, the EPB fixed a criterion for
the firms to get a maximum of 2.5 million taka (50,000 U.S.
dollars) loan without any interest.
</P>
<P>
Last year about 26 firms applied for loans but none of the
firms could fulfill the conditionalities. There were conditions
that a firm must have eight highly qualified computer engineers
who have five years of experiences in the reputed software
development establishments.
</P>
<P>
This condition seemed to be very tough for the loan-seeking
firms. As no firm could meet the condition, the application
scrutiny committee of EPB did not accept application of any firm.
</P>
<P>
Out of this realization, a special committee of EPB on software
has formulated a draft recommendation recently simplifying the
conditions.
</P>
<P>
Under the proposed new conditions, any loan-seeking firm must
have five software engineers with two years of working experience.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
