<HEADLINE> Thai Banks Promotes E-Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Thai banks are moving aggressively
to promote their internet financial services, the Bangkok Post
reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In the past few months, leading Thai banks such as Thai Farmers
Bank, Siam Commercial Bank (SCB) and Bank of Asia, have marketed a
range of new e-services, for example, mobile banking, phone
banking and internet banking, it said.
</P>
<P>
Thai Farmers Bank has set up two new departments for e-services
promotion, one overseeing the bank's internet banking, web page
development and e-commerce, while the other dealing with mobile
and telephone banking, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
SCB has long been a market leader in the development of
electronic banking, and was the first local bank to open an
Automatic Teller Machine (ATM) 18 years ago, it said.
</P>
<P>
Bank of Asia, meanwhile, has formally launched its own e-
commerce services to tap the growth in internet-related services,
said it.
</P>
<P>
Bank executives in the country generally believed that consumer
needs and technological innovation will dominate the development
of financial products in the next few years, according to it.
</P>
