<HEADLINE> Serb Residents Clash With International Police </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, June 21 (Xinhua) --Serb residents clashed with
international police stationed in Kosobska Mitrovica, a northern
Kosovo town on Wednesday. Nineteen Serb civilians were reportedly
injured, two seriously.
</P>
<P>
According to local media, the clash happened while
international policemen were escorting a group of ethnic Albanians
from a southern Albanian community in the direction of a northern
Serb community.
</P>
<P>
Conflicts broke out after a Serb civilian recognized some of
the Albanians as former members of the Kosovo Liberation Army (KLA)
, an armed group of extremist ethnic Albanians, and tried to block
their march.
</P>
<P>
The international policemen used tear-gas, grenades and batons
in an attempt to drive off the Serb civilians.
</P>
<P>
A protest rally in front of the local judicial building
reportedly followed the arrest of one Serb. As the incident
escalated, two Serb civilians were seriously injured by shots
fired by international policemen. Five people were injured by
batons, and 12 others received medical attention from inhaling
tear gas.
</P>
<P>
The incident was finally quelled with the help of the
international peacekeeping troops. The Serb civilian arrested was
later released. International peacekeeping soldiers from France
and Russia have since been patrolling the main roads. 
</P>
</TEXT>
