<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Most Populous Province Successful in Population Growth Control </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Henan, China's most populous
province, has managed to bring its population growth rate under
the national average for eight consecutive years.
</P>
<P>
From 1990 to 1999, the province had 5.6 million fewer babies
being born than expected due to the family planning policy, and
this saved 106 billion yuan of costs for related families and the
state as well.
</P>
<P>
Henan is now home to 93.87 million people. "We still face
population problems because we have a high population base," Vice-
governor Li Zhibin said.
</P>
<P>
Even with a low population growth rate, Henan's population will
continue to increase by 1.2 million annually in the following
decade, he said, adding that rural population accounts for more
than 80 percent of the provincial total.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, the provincial government has begun to provide
better family planning services in a bid to keep a low population
growth rate and improve population quality.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
