<HEADLINE> Update: 33 People Stricken by E-coli Bacteria in Montreal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Nearly 33 people have been stricken
by E-coli bacteria in Montreal. A quebec-based company is
recalling suspected ground beef and hamburger products from 25 of
its chain stores.
</P>
<P>
Provincial government labs in Quebec have found the killer E-
coli bacteria in two samples of the hamburger sold by the company.
</P>
<P>
Canadian health officials have confirmed seven E-coli deaths in
southern Ontario. They are also conducting investigations to
decide if nine other deaths reported recently were linked to the E-
coli outbreak.
</P>
<P>
Water and meat are reported to be the main contamination
source for the spread of E-coli bacteria. 
