Francesco Secchiari won a comfortable victory on the ninth stage,
a 150 km leg from St Moritz to Arosa, at the Tour of Switzerland
cycling race on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Secchiari, who opened an 11-minute advantage on the last major
climb and held off a challenge on the descent to finish three
minutes 34 seconds ahead of compatriot Salvatore Commesso,
finished in three hours 47 minutes 59 seconds..
</P>
<P>
The final kilometers were marked by a succession of attacks and
counter-attacks as Germany's Jan Ullrich and Italians Wladimir
Belli and Dario Frigo tried to snatch their last real chance to
beat race leader Oscar Camenzind of Switzerland ahead of Thursday'
s final stage.
</P>
<P>
But Camenzind and his Lampre Daikin teammates stopped all
attacks and the former world road champion still had 14 seconds
advantage over Frigo on the overall standings. 
