<HEADLINE> Fiji Hostages Expected to Be Freed by Weekend </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Fiji's 31 hostages were expected
to be freed by this weekend, the Australian Broadcasting
Corporation (ABC) said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The ABC quoted military spokesman Filipo Tarakinikini as saying
that he was hoping the hostages could be released by the weekend.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that George Speight and his team are of the same view,
" Tarakinikini said.
</P>
<P>
After days of lengthy negotiations between the military
commander Frank Bainimarama and coup leader George Speight,
lawyers for both sides are scheduled to sign an accord on Thursday
for the installation of a new interim government, the ABC said.
</P>
<P>
The government line-up has not been announced but will likely
include former Vice President Josefa Iloilo as the president and
banker Laisenia Qarase as the prime minister, the ABC said.
</P>
</TEXT>
