<HEADLINE> Residents of 300 Homes Evacuated from Forest Fire in Halifax, Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Residents of more then 300 houses
were evacuated Wednesday as a forest fire approached a community
of 1,000 homes in Halifax, Canada's Atlantic city.
</P>
<P>
At least 40 hectares of forest were reported on fire and
brought under control at one point, only to be whipped up again by
strong winds.
</P>
<P>
Police said Kingswood subdivision is facing a serious threat
with a brush fire burning "right behind its homes."
</P>
<P>
Two helicopters are being used to drop water on the fire, with
two more planes expected to join the fight, according to local
police
</P>
<P>
Firefighters are still battling the blaze, which has as of yet
caused no casualties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
