<DOCNO> XIE20000622.0329 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Netherlands Rally to Beat France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 21 (Xinhua) -- Hosts the Netherlands rallied
strongly from a 2-1 first half down on Wednesday and outplayed
World Cup holders French 3-2 in a showdown of the leading pair of
Group D in the 2000 European championship.
</P>
<P>
In another group D match played in Liege, Czech Republic ousted
Denmark 2-0, both team were stopped their paces to the top eight
at the current tournament.
</P>
<P>
Spain jumped from the third to the top place in group C when
their outlasted Yugoslavia 4-3 with a heroic victory in Bruges of
Belgium. Both Spain and Yugoslavia advanced to the top eight play-
offs which starts on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Also in group C, Norway and Slovenia, both had out of the
quarter-finals, tied in a goalless match in Bruges.
</P>
<P>
France was satisfied with the second spot in the group, though
having their 14-match unbeaten run snapped. The World Champions
sent a powerful warning to all the other quarter-finalists as
their second line-up made the co-hosts struggle for victory.
</P>
<P>
A free-kick thunderbolt from Frank de Boer and a Boudewijn
Zenden run and drive redressed the balance after France built a 2-
1 halftime lead.
</P>
<P>
The Dutch retained home advantage for the knock-out stage where
they are to play Yugoslavia, in a repeat of their last 16 World
Cup encounter, in Rotterdam on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
France will face Spain in the quarter-final as they can keep
their base camp in Belgium.
</P>
<P>
France went ahead 1-0 in the eighth minute through a Christophe
Dugarry header as Dutch goalkeeper Sander Westerveld failed to
reach a Johan Micoud corner.
</P>
<P>
The Dutch equalized six minutes later when Dennis Bergkamp fed
Patrick Kluivert to spring the offside trap. Kluivert ran on to
net his 25th international goal, beating Bernard Lama with a
powerful shot.
</P>
<P>
France took over the lead again in the 31st minute as striker
David Trezeguet diverted a corner into the net as the Dutch
appealed for offside.
</P>
<P>
However, Frank de Boer's free kick in the 51st minute and a
59th minute drive from Zenden after the Dutchman had latched onto
a Westerveld long-ball settled the game. 
</P>
</TEXT>
