<HEADLINE> Canada to Send Trade Mission to Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"This mission is an opportunity for Canadian business to build
on existing Russian partnerships, and further expand into a market
with enormous economic potential," according to Pettigrew.
</P>
<P>
The minister also promised to provide technical support for
Russian accession to the World Trade Organization.
</P>
<P>
The agenda includes a session of the Canada-Russia
Intergovernmental Economic Commission, which was established in
1995 with the purpose of fostering trade, investment and the
transfer of technology between the two countries.
</P>
