<HEADLINE> Peru's Fish Exports Grows 39.2 Pct </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, June 22 (Xinhua) -- The volume of Peru's fish product
exports grew 39.2 percent in May 2000 compared with the same month
of 1999, the Ministry of Fishing reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In May this year, the sector's exports came to 252,300 metric
tons, while in May, 1999, they were 181,300 tons.
</P>
<P>
As regards the amount for fish sales abroad, in May, year 2000,
the amount came to 86.6 million dollars, while in May 1999, it was
75.3 million dollars, according to official figures.
</P>
<P>
Fish products in year 2000's first five months grew 42.9
percent with regard to 1999's same period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
