<HEADLINE> Three Russian Soldiers Drown in Military District Exercise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Three Russian border guards drowned
Thursday during an exercise in Leningrad Military District,
reported the Interfax news agency.
</P>
<P>
The incident occurred while the soldiers were crossing a body
of water in a training center of the military district, which is
located in the settlement of Sertolovo.
</P>
<P>
The servicemen are believed to have been carrying a full combat
load, Interfax cited an official in the press service of Russia's
Northwestern Border Guard Department as saying, not giving other
details.
</P>
<P>
An investigation led by the department deputy chief Sergei
Yerkov is underway, said the report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
