<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wall Street Stocks Fall Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Wall Street stocks fell sharply
Thursday on profit-taking from gains in technology shares.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average closed down 121.62 at 10,376.
12 and the technology heavy Nasdaq composite index fell 127.17 at
3,936.84.
</P>
<P>
Broader stock indicators were also lower. The Standard &AMP; Poor's
500 index fell 26.95 at 1,452.18.
</P>
<P>
The market fell as investors sell technology shares to take
profits from rallies in the previous five straight sessions. The
sellout pulled the Nasdaq index back below the 4,000 mark.
</P>
<P>
The composite climbed to the 4,000 mark just two days ago from
steep falling in April, that pulled the index down 37 percent from
its record closing high of 5,048.62 set on March 10. The index
remains 3.2 percent off this year and 20 percent lower than its
peak.
</P>
<P>
Technology companies that brought down the Nasdaq index today
include Intel, IBM, Yahoo!, Nokia and Micro Technology.
</P>
<P>
The selloff in tech shares spread to the whole market, driving
other indexes lower.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE index fell 7.44 at 641.54 and the American Stock
Exchange index fell 5.31 at 932.91. The Russell 2000 index of
smaller companies fell 12.60 at 515.01.
</P>
<P>
Declining issues outnumbered advancers by an 11-to-6 margin on
the New York Stock Exchange with 1,872 down, 1,015 up and 497
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
NYSE volume increased slightly to 1.01 billion shares from 99.6.
69 million in the previous session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
