<HEADLINE> Mercosur Discusses Cultural Television </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Officials and specialists
from the Southern Common Market (Mercosur) countries analyzed
Thursday here the present situation of Latin American cultural
public television.
</P>
<P>
The meeting entitled " Encounter of Public, Cultural and
Quality Television from Mercosur toward Latin America" was held
within the framework of Mercosur's 10th Culture Ministers' Meeting.
</P>
<P>
Argentine Secretary of Culture and Communication Dario
Loperfido said at the opening session that it has as its target to
fix bases to propitiate a program from public and state channels,
a true and fluid cultural exchange in Latin America, making
conditions suitable for joint co-production and program.
</P>
<P>
He said that regional integration cannot leave out the
cultural factor, and that integration must be respectful of
diversity, of the need for unity and usage of existing resources.
</P>
<P>
In a parallel way, the 10th Meeting of Mercosur Culture
Ministers was being held and  will end Friday, attended by
ministers or vice ministers from Argentina, Brazil, Uruguay,
Paraguay, and other associate countries like Chile and Bolivia.
</P>
</TEXT>
