<HEADLINE> Colombian Paramilitary Troops Murder Nine People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BOGOTA, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Nine people were killed Thursday by
alleged paramilitary troops in two events registered in Colombia's
north and southwest, police sources said.
</P>
<P>
The first act happened in Valencia de Jesus, near Valledupar,
capital of northern Cesar department, where five ranch men and
local businessmen died.
</P>
<P>
The second event took place in Suarez municipality, Valle del
Cauca, where members of the United Autodefenses of Colombia killed
four people, whose identities weren't made known.
</P>
<P>
Last weekend, nine people were murdered in two acts attributed
to paramilitary troops, also in Valle del Cauca. 
</P>
</TEXT>
