<HEADLINE> Argentine Stocks Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, June 22 (Xinhua) -- The leading Merval index on
the Buenos Aires Exchange closed down 1.30 percent at 478.42
points Thursday compared with Wednesday's 484.77 points.
</P>
<P>
The turnover was 58.66 million U.S. dollars against 60.085
million dollars in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The annual inter-bank interest rate fell to 7.25 percent from 7.
45 percent in the 24-hour term. The exchange rate of the Argentine
peso against the U.S. dollar quoted at 0.997 for purchase and 1.
002 for sale. 
