<HEADLINE> Mexican Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, June 22 (Xinhua) -- The Mexican Stock Exchange
closed lower Thursday with the benchmark IPC index falling by 116.
33 points, or 1.74 percent, to 6,570.64 points.
</P>
<P>
Dealers exchanged 74.244 million shares worth some 148.082
million U.S. dollars against Wednesday's 131.539 million shares
worth some 180.311 million dollars.
</P>
