<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 4.0 Degree Earthquake Shakes Nicaragua </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, June 22 (Xinhua) -- A four-degree quake on the Richter
scale Thursday shook Nicaragua's Pacific, reported the Nicaraguan
Institute of Land Studies (INETER).
</P>
<P>
INETER said in a communique that the tremor happened at 11:49
local time and had its epicenter at 10.42 degrees northern
latitude and 86.40 degrees western longitude, or 192 kilometers
south of the capital, Managua.
</P>
<P>
INETER explained the earthquake is an event related with
tectonic processes of collision between Cocos' and Caribe's
plaques. 
</P>
</TEXT>
