<HEADLINE> Mexican Oil Exports To Go Up to 75,000 Bpd </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO, June 22 (Xinhua) -- Mexico will increase by 75,000
barrels daily (bpd) of its oil exports starting on July 1 to
contribute to stabilizing the international market.
</P>
<P>
The Secretariat of Energy said in a communique that with this
additional amount of exports, Mexico will export 1.745 million bpd
of oil starting July 1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
